{
  "stem": "25651.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Hubbolt, ?] a Czech, quite a nice man, historian.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first question I asked him, what have you done with the organ?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER] Of course, the organ is gone because the synagogue was devastated in 1938 during the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that's an interesting question because we were six boys.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm the youngest of six boys--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, the eldest was Leo.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He-- he became Dr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Leo Honigwachs in 1938.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He went to the University of Brno.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now he went to German schools, German gymnasium, and his mother tongue was German because the town was a German Sudetenland town.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in 1918, when Czechoslovakia became Czechoslovakia, there wasn't a single Czech school in the town, not even an elementary school.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So he went entirely through German schools, and then when he went to university, he had to swap over from German to Czech.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in fact, his first two years at university were very difficult because his professors used to say to him, you know, your essays are unacceptable.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "If-- if you want to be a doctor, the first thing you have to learn is how to speak properly because he didn't know Czech.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that was rather difficult.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The second one was Henry, Hermann in German or Heinrich.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "His Hebrew name was [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He also went to German schools-- German Gymnasium-- and he then went to a German speaking trade school.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he went into my father's business and his mother tongue was German.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He spoke some Czech, very haltingly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Now the third one is [INAUDIBLE] or [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Shragga, ?] in Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Ferdinand or Fritz, we used to call him, but in the Jewish Youth Movement, we called him [?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Alif, ?] so multiplicity of names because of different languages.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But he went to elementary school in German.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
